This landing page was developed as part of the Oasis Infobyte Web Development Internship (Level 1). The main objective of this project was to create a visually appealing, responsive and user-friendly landing page using only HTML5 and CSS3. While working on this project, I focused on creating a clean layout, proper spacing, attractive colors and a responsive design that provides a good user experience on different screen sizes.

The landing page includes a modern navigation bar, hero section, call-to-action button and well-structured content sections. CSS Flexbox and Grid were used to create a responsive layout, while hover effects, transitions and media queries were implemented to improve the overall look and feel of the website. The design automatically adjusts according to different devices such as desktops, tablets and smartphones.

This project helped me strengthen my understanding of HTML structure, semantic elements, CSS styling, responsive web design and layout techniques. It also improved my ability to organize code, design attractive user interfaces and build projects using best development practices.

During the development process, I learned how to structure a webpage properly, write clean and reusable CSS code, and make websites responsive for different screen sizes. This project also enhanced my problem-solving skills by allowing me to overcome layout and styling challenges while building the website.

Technologies Used:
• HTML5
• CSS3

